    • Constructor Detail

      • BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH

        public BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH()
        Create an object that holds a null BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH obj = new BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH, use the static "constructor" : 
          BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH obj = BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

      • asBASS_BFX_AUTOWAH

        public static BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH asBASS_BFX_AUTOWAH(Pointer pointer)
        Create a view of the Pointer object as a BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH object.
        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a BASS_BFX_AUTOWAH object.
